  "dateModified": "2026-03-05",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A **reflexive deficit** is the condition in which a system operates with high first-order competence — correcting errors, responding to inputs, adapting outputs — but lacks the second-order capacity to monitor whether its own operational frame remains appropriate to the situation it is meant to serve.",
  "keywords": "cybernetics, organizational-theory",
  "name": "Reflexive Deficit",
